      "content": "I recommend using an embedded memory profiler like Valgrind (if hardware supports it), ChipIDE's heap usage tools, or a lightweight custom allocator tracker to monitor heap growth over time. Since this is an automotive context, ensure you are running under strict real-time constraints and consider using a heap sanitization library specifically designed for safety-critical systems. Once you isolate the memory growth pattern, cross-reference it with your build logs and developer memory regions to identify which allocation or dynamic structure growth is causing the issue.",
